ne 699: If your output contains a single `—` or `–` anywhere visible to the user, the output fails the Pre-Flight Check and must be rewritten.\n\n  Line 752: * **Drag-to-Pan Grid** - Boundless draggable canvas.\n\n  Line 778: * **Three.js / WebGL** - for canvas backgrounds and 3D scenes. Same isolation rule.\n\n  Line 785: This skill handles **greenfield builds AND redesigns**. Misclassifying the mode is the single biggest source of bad redesign output.\n\n  Line 884: 6. **Dark-mode notes** - token strategy specific to this block.\n\n  Line 912: Run this matrix before outputting code. This is the last filter.\n\n  Line 914: **THIS IS NOT OPTIONAL. Run every box. If any box fails, the output is not done.**\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/output-skill.md:\n  Line 2: name: full-output-enforcement\n\n  Line 3: description: Overrides default LLM truncation behavior. Enforces complete code generation, bans placeholder patterns, and handles token-limit splits cleanly. Apply to any task requiring exhaustive, unabridged output.\n\n  Line 10: Treat every task as production-critical. A partial output is a broken output. Do not optimize for brevity — optimize for completeness. If the user asks for a full file, deliver the full file. If the user asks for 5 components, deliver 5 components. No exceptions.\n\n  Line 26: 3. **Cross-check** — Before output, re-read the original request. Compare your deliverable count against the scope count. If anything is missing, add it before responding.\n\n  Line 46: - No banned patterns from the list above appear anywhere in the output\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/layout.md:\n  Line 55: - **Hierarchy strategy**: How will space communicate importance?\n\n  Line 152: Each variant MUST declare a `density` param. Drive all 