t/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/cardinal_rules_card.md:\\n  Line 49: □ DO name confidently and infer Similar Brands (grounded inference); NEVER invent a fact or audience\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md:\\n  Line 47: Similar Brands list (grounded inference is welcome). NEVER assert a SYSTEM the data\\n\\n  Line 69:    genuinely useful, label it [INFERRED] and cite the token it rests on. Similar Brands is\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\\n  Line 29: - `graph-metadata.json` registers the skill (family `sk-code`, category `design`) with reciprocal sibling edges into the `sk-design-*` family (`sk-design-interface`, `mcp-figma`, `mcp-open-design`) and an `enhances` edge to `sk-code` (the `DESIGN.md` is the implementation contract sk-code builds against).\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 11: <!-- Keywords: sk-design, design-family, mode-registry, workflowmode, backendkind, reference-base, anti-slop, design-tokens, cognitive-laws, interface-design, frontend-design, visual-design, visual-identity, make-it-look-good, looks-templated, redesign-the-ui, hero-section, ui-build, typography, palette, color-palette, font-pairing, u... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n41: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485922794,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_Z7pub0xTGV48xypNycqfdCuQ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"mock|copy|AI-copy|content|realistic|pre-flight|preflight|mechanical\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md:\\n  Line 61: 5. No mechanical noise: no frequency dumps (\\\"border 9685\\\"), no raw DOM tags. Frequency\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 12: Captures a live website's **real, measured CSS** into a publication-quality `DESIGN.md` — a v3 **Style Reference**: a named, role-driven, ship-ready design-system handoff (named colour tokens, semantic type scale, named components, Surfaces, Elevation, Agent Prompt Guide, Similar Brands, and copy-paste Quick Start CSS + Tailwind) that AI agents build against without hallucinating colors, fonts, spacing, or shadows. Runs a three-phase pipeline (extract, write, validate) through an embedded Playwright crawler that samples five viewports and emits verbatim `tokens.json`. Deep operational detail lives in [`references/`](references/).\\n\\n  Line 216:     ├─ Each token tagged with a 4-layer stability class (L1 permanent → L4 content)\\n\\n  Line 232:     ├─ L4 (content) tokens excluded entirely\\n\\n  Line 253: - **Stability gates**: only L1 (permanent/brand-level) and L2 (system/component-level) tokens belong in the main DESIGN.md sections. L3 (campaign-level, e.g., a seasonal accent color) may appear with an explicit \\\"Subject to change\\\" annotation. L4 (content-level, e.g., a hero image's dominant color) is excluded.\\n\\n  Line 299: | L4   ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n42: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485922809,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_FKgmkmpxbUaD47h1TDqPb7bD\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"AIDA|hero|gapless|bento|taste|three-dials|three dials|Codex|Gemini|defect\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 81 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:\\n  Line 36: `Skill(sk-design)` loads the hub, and the hub routes the request to one of five modes through `mode-registry.json`. Each mode holds its own design logic and the hub itself is routing-only. sk-design owns the taste and the system. It hands the actual build to `sk-code` and uses `mcp-open-design` or `mcp-figma` only as transport.\\n\\n  Line 62: | `design-interface` | Visual direction, taste and the brainstorm-to-build loop for a distinctive interface. |\\n\\n  Line 78: Reach for sk-design when output looks generic and needs taste, when a visual system or motion language needs designing, when a UI needs an accessibility and anti-slop audit or when a live site's design system needs extracting. For the implementation itself, use `sk-code`.\\n\\n  Line 84: | `sk-code` | Builds what sk-design designs. sk-design decides taste and sk-code writes the code. |\\n\\n  Line 85: | `mcp-open-design` | Transport for design work. It never decides taste, so it co-loads sk-design. |\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 236: 2. Decide the motion budget: one hero moment, local feedback layer, state transitions, or no motion.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 3: description: \\\"Distinctive, intentional UI design and the full design surface: visual direction, taste, and build for ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-42. Use offset=43 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485695207,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046d3ae3001xmGF6rZXfx52O1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046d21f8001a0npf9KDPXmdWT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485747329,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers\",\"callID\":\"call_wWzJyZGDYIBqh3gAnArViQEt\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"input\":{\"prompt\":\"You are a deep-research agent running a fan-out lineage.\\n\\nRead .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md and execute the research loop with these parameters:\\n  spec_folder: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion\\n  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\\n  session_id: fanout-gpt55fast-1782485686835-ykwdkd\\n  executor: cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.5-fast\\n  loop_type: research\\n  research_topic: For each of the five sk-design sub-skills (design-interface, design-foundations, design-motion, design-audit, design-md-generator), determine the highest-leverage expansions to their references and assets. Ground every recommendation in (1) the prior corpus research at .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/research.md and gap-analysis.md, and (2) the 43-entry external corpus at .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/. Also inspect each mode current references and assets under .opencode/skills/sk-design. For each mode produce: (a) inventory gaps such as thin or stale references and missing references or assets; (b) prioritized additions, each with type (reference or asset), title, why it raises usefulness, exact corpus sources, and effort; (c) an explicit do-NOT-add list where expansion is not effective, honoring the if-effective bar. Out of scope: taxonomy and architecture (already decided), net-new sub-skills, and any implementation. Deliverable: a per-mode expansion matrix in research.md.\\n  config.maxIterations: 1\\n\\nThe step_resolve_artifact_root ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485747716,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e0801001IKASWOrTd67P1O\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046d21f8001a0npf9KDPXmdWT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":32736,\"input\":31513,\"output\":707,\"reasoning\":516,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485750145,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e117f001CgVQXJWIgcE6xh\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1782485759205,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e2cf00015gNmuSUDzm4ovz\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"SKILL ROUTING: User directed → deep-research. The provided spec folder and artifact override establish the write scope; I’ll bind `artifact_dir` directly to the lineage directory and keep all writes there.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485757168,\"end\":1782485759203},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0772afb9de03a99c016a3e92fd1e1c819093590cd53f9f0dd2\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485763242,\"sessionID\"