ll Preload Mandate\\\",\\n          \\\"importanceTier\\\": \\\"constitutional\\\",\\n          \\\"retrieval_directive\\\": \\\"Always surface when: rule applies — MUST `Read` `.opencode/s... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485763564,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e45e8001XbwkLhoe9YjqAL\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":33342,\"input\":1769,\"output\":163,\"reasoning\":178,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":31232}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485766371,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e50e2001m4uDtuZKw0cMKb\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e4723001i7Bx5U8Kbk92Yg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485776260,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_IUnAEA1EdTz1UF8VE7gkayNY\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-research\\n3: description: \\\"Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]\\n5: argument-hint: \\\"[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\\\"\\n6: version: 1.14.0.0\\n7: ---\\n8: \\n9: <!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\\n10: \\n11: # Autonomous Deep Research Loop\\n12: \\n13: Note: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\\n14: \\n15: Iterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\\n16: \\n17: Runtime path resolution:\\n18: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\\n19: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\\n20: - Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\\n21: \\n22: Operator contract precedence for this skill surface:\\n23: - Command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n24: - Convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow\\n25: - Runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories ab... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485776651,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e7908001D5FlQalcLSTkxD\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e4723001i7Bx5U8Kbk92Yg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":35710,\"input\":2702,\"output\":63,\"reasoning\":177,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":32768}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485778505,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e8048001Sg7qzH9TJafLsL\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1782485822058,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046edb17001CJqifYvweS4U1y\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Artifact scope is constrained to the lineage directory. I’m loading the deep-research protocol resources and source corpus now, then I’ll write only the lineage state, iteration, and synthesis artifacts under `research/lineages/gpt55fast`.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485801751,\"end\":1782485822053},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_08d7b9b3c089c314016a3e9329b63c8194a5ea4c6648e21ce6\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822113,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_UboDjjapGF6vOSUq09lYVkzL\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep research quick reference\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop cheat sheet\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration checklist\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research loop troubleshooting\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research tuning guide\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research progress visualization\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: general\\n13: version: 1.14.0.26\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Quick Reference\\n17: \\n18: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\\n25: \\n26: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\\n27: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n28: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\\n30: \\n31: ---\\n32: \\n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\\n34: \\n3... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_ZKm0jZheDlLTMbONMRBCx38A\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast</path>\\n<type>directory</type>\\n<entries>\\n.executor-state/\\n\\n(1 entries)\\n</entries>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\".executor-state/\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[],\"display\":{\"type\":\"directory\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"entries\":[\".executor-state/\"],\"offset\":1,\"totalEntries\":1,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485822120,\"end\":1782485822122}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_08d7b9b3c089c314016a3e933dfc24819488bc35add94f007f\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f046f2aa7001BHAyfigtbl6J73\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_OF9AysmYOE439QGLkMVY4y02\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: State Format Reference\\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state format\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research state packet hub\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research file ownership model\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research file protection rules\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research packet location\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # State Format Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\\n30: \\n31: ### Routed Details\\n32: \\n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\\n36: \\n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_PjoHAe1tEzjqEoz3p1l6lT6E\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state jsonl\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research config record\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration records\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research negative knowledge\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research graph events\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research event records\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n17: \\n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\\n39: \\n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\\n41: \\n42: ```json\\n43: {\\n4... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_x00KCnKA4Xh8qFQZMCmYpB05\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research output files\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research iteration files\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research synthesis document\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research resource map\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research strategy file\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"spec anchoring output\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n17: \\n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\\n39: \\n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\\n41: \\n42: Required sections:\\n43: \\n... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_xhfVwOsuCU3iWF2DTtwcZWjC\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research auto resume protocol\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research pause sentinel\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research synthesis phase\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: important\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\\n17: \\n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle tr... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_sTpU6xJ9wOPuhGVJrrU6HtrA\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research convergence detection\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research stop contract\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research stopreason values\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research legal stop gates\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research convergence decision order\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\\n30: \\n31: ### Key Sources\\n32: \\n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\\n38... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822133,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_dyDSntQay0nbNT6Ok5VK5aNu\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Convergence Signals Reference\\n3: description: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research convergence signals\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research new info ratio\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research stuck count\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"mad noise floor\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"question entropy\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research composite score\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"convergence threshold tuning\\\"\\n12: importance_tier: normal\\n13: contextType: implementation\\n14: version: 1.14.0.3\\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: # Convergence Signals Reference\\n18: \\n19: This reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\\n20: \\n21: ---\\n22: \\n23: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n24: \\n25: ### Purpose\\n26: \\n27: Define the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\\n28: \\n29: ### When to Use\\n30: \\n31: Load this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\\n32: \\n33: ### Core Principle\\n34: \\n35: Signals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\\n36: \\n37: ---\\n38: \\n39: ## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\\n40: \\n41: The live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\\n42: \\n43: | Signal | Weig... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast/logs/fanout-lineage.out","text":"{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485695207,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046d3ae3001xmGF6rZXfx52O1\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046d21f8001a0npf9KDPXmdWT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485747329,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers\",\"callID\":\"call_wWzJyZGDYIBqh3gAnArViQEt\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"error\",\"input\":{\"prompt\":\"You are a deep-research agent running a fan-out lineage.\\n\\nRead .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md and execute the research loop with these parameters:\\n  spec_folder: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion\\n  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\\n  session_id: fanout-gpt55fast-1782485686835-ykwdkd\\n  executor: cli-opencode model=openai/gpt-5.5-fast\\n  loop_type: research\\n  research_topic: For each of the five sk-design sub-skills (design-interface, design-foundations, design-motion, design-audit, design-md-generator), determine the highest-leverage expansions to their references and assets. Ground every recommendation in (1) the prior corpus research at .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/research.md and gap-analysis.md, and (2) the 43-entry external corpus at .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/. Also inspect each mode current references and assets under .opencode/skills/sk-design. For each mode produce: (a) inventory gaps such as thin or stale references and missing references or assets; (b) prioritized additions, each with type (reference or asset), title, why it raises usefulness, exact corpus sources, and effort; (c) an explicit do-NOT-add list where expansion is not effective, honoring the if-effective bar. Out of scope: taxonomy and architecture (already decided), net-new sub-skills, and any implementation. Deliverable: a per-mode expansion matrix in research.md.\\n  config.maxIterations: 1\\n\\nThe step_resolve_artifact_root ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485747716,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e0801001IKASWOrTd67P1O\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046d21f8001a0npf9KDPXmdWT\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":32736,\"input\":31513,\"output\":707,\"reasoning\":516,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":0}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485750145,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e117f001CgVQXJWIgcE6xh\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1782485759205,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e2cf00015gNmuSUDzm4ovz\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"SKILL ROUTING: User directed → deep-research. The provided spec folder and artifact override establish the write scope; I’ll bind `artifact_dir` directly to the lineage directory and keep all writes there.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485757168,\"end\":1782485759203},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0772afb9de03a99c016a3e92fd1e1c819093590cd53f9f0dd2\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485763242,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"mk-spec-memory_memory_match_triggers\",\"callID\":\"call_7jqdRe07setkUIy2K76rRqLJ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"prompt\":\"deep-research fan-out lineage for sk-design reference asset expansion matrix; inspect prior corpus research and current sk-design references/assets; write lineage outputs only under gpt55fast artifact directory\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion\",\"tenantId\":\"\",\"userId\":\"\",\"agentId\":\"\",\"limit\":5,\"session_id\":\"\",\"turnNumber\":1,\"include_cognitive\":false},\"output\":\"{\\n  \\\"summary\\\": \\\"No matching trigger phrases found\\\",\\n  \\\"data\\\": {\\n    \\\"count\\\": 0,\\n    \\\"results\\\": [],\\n    \\\"matchType\\\": \\\"trigger-phrase\\\",\\n    \\\"degradedMatching\\\": null,\\n    \\\"triggerSignals\\\": [],\\n    \\\"cognitive\\\": null\\n  },\\n  \\\"hints\\\": [\\n    \\\"Ensure memories have trigger phrases defined\\\",\\n    \\\"Try a different prompt or check memory content\\\",\\n    \\\"Auto-surface hook: injected 10 constitutional and 5 triggered memories (440ms)\\\"\\n  ],\\n  \\\"meta\\\": {\\n    \\\"tool\\\": \\\"memory_match_triggers\\\",\\n    \\\"tokenCount\\\": 2180,\\n    \\\"latencyMs\\\": 11,\\n    \\\"cacheHit\\\": false,\\n    \\\"autoSurface\\\": {\\n      \\\"constitutionalCount\\\": 10,\\n      \\\"triggeredCount\\\": 5,\\n      \\\"surfaced_at\\\": \\\"2026-06-26T14:56:03.224Z\\\",\\n      \\\"latencyMs\\\": 440\\n    },\\n    \\\"autoSurfacedContext\\\": {\\n      \\\"constitutional\\\": [\\n        {\\n          \\\"id\\\": 21863,\\n          \\\"specFolder\\\": \\\"system-spec-kit\\\",\\n          \\\"filePath\\\": \\\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/cli-dispatch-skill-preload.md\\\",\\n          \\\"title\\\": \\\"CLI DISPATCH — Skill Preload Mandate\\\",\\n          \\\"importanceTier\\\": \\\"constitutional\\\",\\n          \\\"retrieval_directive\\\": \\\"Always surface when: rule applies — MUST `Read` `.opencode/s... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485763564,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e45e8001XbwkLhoe9YjqAL\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e09ac001ux39zMiYCLeq2q\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":33342,\"input\":1769,\"output\":163,\"reasoning\":178,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":31232}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485766371,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e50e2001m4uDtuZKw0cMKb\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e4723001i7Bx5U8Kbk92Yg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485776260,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_IUnAEA1EdTz1UF8VE7gkayNY\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: name: deep-research\\n3: description: \\\"Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation, externalized state, convergence detection, fresh context per pass.\\\"\\n4: allowed-tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, memory_context, memory_search]\\n5: argument-hint: \\\"[topic] [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N]\\\"\\n6: version: 1.14.0.0\\n7: ---\\n8: \\n9: <!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\\n10: \\n11: # Autonomous Deep Research Loop\\n12: \\n13: Note: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\\n14: \\n15: Iterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\\n16: \\n17: Runtime path resolution:\\n18: - OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\\n19: - Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\\n20: - Codex runtime: `.codex/agents/*.toml`\\n21: \\n22: Operator contract precedence for this skill surface:\\n23: - Command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n24: - Convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow\\n25: - Runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories ab... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485776651,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e7908001D5FlQalcLSTkxD\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e4723001i7Bx5U8Kbk92Yg\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":35710,\"input\":2702,\"output\":63,\"reasoning\":177,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":32768}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485778505,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046e8048001Sg7qzH9TJafLsL\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1782485822058,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046edb17001CJqifYvweS4U1y\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Artifact scope is constrained to the lineage directory. I’m loading the deep-research protocol resources and source corpus now, then I’ll write only the lineage state, iteration, and synthesis artifacts under `research/lineages/gpt55fast`.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485801751,\"end\":1782485822053},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_08d7b9b3c089c314016a3e9329b63c8194a5ea4c6648e21ce6\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822113,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_UboDjjapGF6vOSUq09lYVkzL\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep research quick reference\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop cheat sheet\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration checklist\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research loop troubleshooting\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research tuning guide\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research progress visualization\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: general\\n13: version: 1.14.0.26\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Quick Reference\\n17: \\n18: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\\n25: \\n26: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\\n27: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n28: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\\n30: \\n31: ---\\n32: \\n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\\n34: \\n3... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_ZKm0jZheDlLTMbONMRBCx38A\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast</path>\\n<type>directory</type>\\n<entries>\\n.executor-state/\\n\\n(1 entries)\\n</entries>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\".executor-state/\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[],\"display\":{\"type\":\"directory\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"entries\":[\".executor-state/\"],\"offset\":1,\"totalEntries\":1,\"truncated\":false}},\"title\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485822120,\"end\":1782485822122}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_08d7b9b3c089c314016a3e933dfc24819488bc35add94f007f\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f046f2aa7001BHAyfigtbl6J73\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_OF9AysmYOE439QGLkMVY4y02\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: State Format Reference\\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state format\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research state packet hub\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research file ownership model\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research file protection rules\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research packet location\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # State Format Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\\n30: \\n31: ### Routed Details\\n32: \\n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\\n36: \\n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_PjoHAe1tEzjqEoz3p1l6lT6E\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research state jsonl\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research config record\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research iteration records\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research negative knowledge\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research graph events\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research event records\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\\n17: \\n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\\n39: \\n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\\n41: \\n42: ```json\\n43: {\\n4... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_x00KCnKA4Xh8qFQZMCmYpB05\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research output files\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research iteration files\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research synthesis document\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research resource map\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research strategy file\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"spec anchoring output\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\\n17: \\n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\\n35: \\n36: ---\\n37: \\n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\\n39: \\n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\\n41: \\n42: Required sections:\\n43: \\n... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_xhfVwOsuCU3iWF2DTtwcZWjC\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research loop protocol\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research loop lifecycle\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research loop initialization\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research auto resume protocol\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research pause sentinel\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research synthesis phase\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: important\\n12: contextType: implementation\\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\\n17: \\n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n23: \\n24: ### Purpose\\n25: \\n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\\n27: \\n28: ### When to Use\\n29: \\n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\\n31: \\n32: ### Core Principle\\n33: \\n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle tr... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822130,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_sTpU6xJ9wOPuhGVJrrU6HtrA\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research convergence detection\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research stop contract\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research stopreason values\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"research legal stop gates\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research convergence decision order\\\"\\n10: importance_tier: important\\n11: contextType: implementation\\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\\n13: ---\\n14: \\n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\\n16: \\n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\\n18: \\n19: ---\\n20: \\n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n22: \\n23: ### Purpose\\n24: \\n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\\n26: \\n27: ### When to Use\\n28: \\n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\\n30: \\n31: ### Key Sources\\n32: \\n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\\n38... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485822133,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_dyDSntQay0nbNT6Ok5VK5aNu\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Convergence Signals Reference\\n3: description: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"research convergence signals\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research new info ratio\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research stuck count\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"mad noise floor\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"question entropy\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"research composite score\\\"\\n11:   - \\\"convergence threshold tuning\\\"\\n12: importance_tier: normal\\n13: contextType: implementation\\n14: version: 1.14.0.3\\n15: ---\\n16: \\n17: # Convergence Signals Reference\\n18: \\n19: This reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\\n20: \\n21: ---\\n22: \\n23: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n24: \\n25: ### Purpose\\n26: \\n27: Define the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\\n28: \\n29: ### When to Use\\n30: \\n31: Load this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\\n32: \\n33: ### Core Principle\\n34: \\n35: Signals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\\n36: \\n37: ---\\n38: \\n39: ## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\\n40: \\n41: The live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\\n42: \\n43: | Signal | Weig... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485822824,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046f2d65001CbpOMSxp32KIeQ\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046e7a410019J9A6Ap2ersiET\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":44609,\"input\":8088,\"output\":571,\"reasoning\":622,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":35328}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485824959,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f046f35be001GiM3sFF3L1egD0\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046f2ea600130GfF8lylDSVO9\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485857465,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_zQGEG0SaMIoqHXxk7Vygfd4X\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/skills/sk-design/**/references/**/*.md\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/critique_hardening.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/anti_patterns_production.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/audit_contract.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/corpus_map.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/references/accessibility_performance.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/motion_strategy.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/micro_interactions.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/corpus_map.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/performance_reduced_motion.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/references/animate_presence_patterns.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/references/quality_checklist.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-desig... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485857465,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_MClFttMQLqV9VKfxHtuiDQnG\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/**/*\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"No files found\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":0,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485857135,\"end\":1782485857463}},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"fc_0f3db47b8147bb0c016a3e93610bac819190e1df2d21bef6ca\"}},\"id\":\"prt_f046fb351001VVaD3vWAXAc3Jn\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046f2ea600130GfF8lylDSVO9\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485857496,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_iBywpPuTeY9riRJvRmYWGEgJ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/gap-analysis.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/gap-analysis.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Corpus Gap Analysis — content the sk-design family does not yet cover\\n2: \\n3: > **Packet:** `154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research` · **Companion to** `research.md` (this folder's *architecture* synthesis). Different question.\\n4: > **Question:** Of the external design-skills corpus, what techniques / topics are MISSING or under-covered in the converted `sk-design` family (`design-interface`, `design-foundations`, `design-motion`, `design-audit`, `design-md-generator`), and what should be added?\\n5: > **Status:** **CURRENT-STATE VALIDATED.** Severities are validated against the post-conversion `design-<mode>` family. **ADD decisions are GATED** — nothing here is implemented.\\n6: > **Provenance:** a 2-model fan-out produced a 16-gap baseline (recovered from a completed run's logs after an in-sandbox write-block); that baseline was then **re-validated by a current-state Opus-4.8 pass** against the converted family — it read all 5 packet SKILL.md + `shared/` + the corpus, confirmed 15/16, marked 0 now-covered, revised 5 severities/framings, reclassified 2 as scope rulings, and added 3 new gaps (N1–N3). The full per-gap prose lives in `scratchpad/gap-research/run2/opus.log`.\\n7: \\n8: ## Verdict\\n9: \\n10: Baseline substantially correct: **15 confirmed, 0 now-covered, 5 revised, +3 new (N1–N3).** Two baseline items (13 proces... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485857507,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_3uFRxhHAyWPSJ9HqtEl9VD3b\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/research.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":2000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research/research/research.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Deep-Research Synthesis — Restructuring `sk-design-interface` into an `sk-design` Parent\\n2: \\n3: > **Packet:** `154-sk-design-parent/001-corpus-research` · **Loop:** deep-research (4-model fan-out) · **Status:** consolidated synthesis for the phase-002 architecture decision gate.\\n4: > **Question:** How to restructure the existing `sk-design-interface` skill into a PARENT skill `sk-design` containing 4–7 focused design SUB-SKILLS, grounded in the external design-skills corpus. Three outputs: (1) optimal sub-skill taxonomy with scope + corpus sources; (2) structural-model evidence (single hub with nested mode packets vs. umbrella router over a sibling family); (3) per-child onboarding + backward-compat, folding in `sk-design-interface` and `sk-design-md-generator`.\\n5: \\n6: ---\\n7: \\n8: ## 1. Summary\\n9: \\n10: All four model lineages independently conclude that `sk-design` should be a **family of focused design sub-skills under one parent**, and that the existing internal split — visual *invention* (`sk-design-interface`) vs. measured *extraction* (`sk-design-md-generator`) — is the correct seam to generalize. Three of four lineages (opus48-claude2, gpt55fast, mimo25pro) recommend the **umbrella-router-over-siblings** structural model; one (kimi27) dissents toward a **hub-with-nested-packets** model on advisor-identity grounds. The... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485857533,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"glob\",\"callID\":\"call_EIWvVNUvsbSYbXIyUs8KijWd\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\".opencode/skills/sk-design/**/SKILL.md\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public\"},\"output\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-foundations/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-audit/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-interface/SKILL.md\",\"metadata\":{\"count\":6,\"truncated\":false},\"title\":\"\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485857215,\"end\