kill.md\\nslidev.md\\nsoft-skill.md\\nstitch-skill.md\\ntaste-skill.md\\nui-skills-root.md\\n\\n(43 entries)\\n</entries>\",\"metadata\":{\"preview\":\"12-principles-of-animation.md\\nadapt.md\\nanimate.md\\napple-bento-grid-main/\\naudit.md\\nbaseline.md\\nbencium-innovative-ux-designer.md\\nbolder.md\\nbrutalist-skill.md\\ncanvas-design.md\\nclarify.md\\ncolorize.md\\ncritique.md\\ndelight.md\\ndesign-lab.md\\ndesigner-skills-main/\\ndistill.md\\nemil-design-eng.md\\nfixing-accessibility.md\\nfixing-motion-performance.md\",\"truncated\":false,\"loaded\":[],\"display\":{\"type\":\"directory\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external\",\"entries\":[\"12-principles-of-animatio... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1782485883997,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f04701c5b001P7eoa6qhWjE07v\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f046ff0e2001Muntq2QbMjRBx4\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":78980,\"input\":535,\"output\":109,\"reasoning\":0,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":78336}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1782485886308,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f0470256300156cnGM1B4ebwtl\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f04701d99001dniLSnsg6mu862\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"snapshot\":\"3e6cc433f6fa417b5febd6fff1136f1400809b80\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"text\",\"timestamp\":1782485922666,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f047068c7001Sm76hONMc53bpK\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f04701d99001dniLSnsg6mu862\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Current `sk-design` has broad child references but only two assets, both in `design-md-generator`; the next pass is checking whether the known gap-analysis items are actually covered in the live child references.\",\"time\":{\"start\":1782485903559,\"end\":1782485922659},\"metadata\":{\"openai\":{\"itemId\":\"msg_0fdb965002fe82d5016a3e938f8e688191865c2b5bd34f812e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}}}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485922748,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_ksyzgeOBFOUYYYuMqRBIMO1S\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"brand|Brand|product|Product|register|Register|bolder|quieter|distill|transform\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/cardinal_rules_card.md:\\n  Line 49: □ DO name confidently and infer Similar Brands (grounded inference); NEVER invent a fact or audience\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md:\\n  Line 47: Similar Brands list (grounded inference is welcome). NEVER assert a SYSTEM the data\\n\\n  Line 69:    genuinely useful, label it [INFERRED] and cite the token it rests on. Similar Brands is\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\\n  Line 29: - `graph-metadata.json` registers the skill (family `sk-code`, category `design`) with reciprocal sibling edges into the `sk-design-*` family (`sk-design-interface`, `mcp-figma`, `mcp-open-design`) and an `enhances` edge to `sk-code` (the `DESIGN.md` is the implementation contract sk-code builds against).\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 11: <!-- Keywords: sk-design, design-family, mode-registry, workflowmode, backendkind, reference-base, anti-slop, design-tokens, cognitive-laws, interface-design, frontend-design, visual-design, visual-identity, make-it-look-good, looks-templated, redesign-the-ui, hero-section, ui-build, typography, palette, color-palette, font-pairing, u... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485922794,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_Z7pub0xTGV48xypNycqfdCuQ\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"mock|copy|AI-copy|content|realistic|pre-flight|preflight|mechanical\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/assets/design_md_prompt_template.md:\\n  Line 61: 5. No mechanical noise: no frequency dumps (\\\"border 9685\\\"), no raw DOM tags. Frequency\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-md-generator/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 12: Captures a live website's **real, measured CSS** into a publication-quality `DESIGN.md` — a v3 **Style Reference**: a named, role-driven, ship-ready design-system handoff (named colour tokens, semantic type scale, named components, Surfaces, Elevation, Agent Prompt Guide, Similar Brands, and copy-paste Quick Start CSS + Tailwind) that AI agents build against without hallucinating colors, fonts, spacing, or shadows. Runs a three-phase pipeline (extract, write, validate) through an embedded Playwright crawler that samples five viewports and emits verbatim `tokens.json`. Deep operational detail lives in [`references/`](references/).\\n\\n  Line 216:     ├─ Each token tagged with a 4-layer stability class (L1 permanent → L4 content)\\n\\n  Line 232:     ├─ L4 (content) tokens excluded entirely\\n\\n  Line 253: - **Stability gates**: only L1 (permanent/brand-level) and L2 (system/component-level) tokens belong in the main DESIGN.md sections. L3 (campaign-level, e.g., a seasonal accent color) may appear with an explicit \\\"Subject to change\\\" annotation. L4 (content-level, e.g., a hero image's dominant color) is excluded.\\n\\n  Line 299: | L4   ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1782485922809,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0fb92e263ffeALnyZrQY8DwEJB\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"grep\",\"callID\":\"call_FKgmkmpxbUaD47h1TDqPb7bD\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"pattern\":\"AIDA|hero|gapless|bento|taste|three-dials|three dials|Codex|Gemini|defect\",\"path\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design\",\"include\":\"*.md\"},\"output\":\"Found 81 matches\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/README.md:\\n  Line 36: `Skill(sk-design)` loads the hub, and the hub routes the request to one of five modes through `mode-registry.json`. Each mode holds its own design logic and the hub itself is routing-only. sk-design owns the taste and the system. It hands the actual build to `sk-code` and uses `mcp-open-design` or `mcp-figma` only as transport.\\n\\n  Line 62: | `design-interface` | Visual direction, taste and the brainstorm-to-build loop for a distinctive interface. |\\n\\n  Line 78: Reach for sk-design when output looks generic and needs taste, when a visual system or motion language needs designing, when a UI needs an accessibility and anti-slop audit or when a live site's design system needs extracting. For the implementation itself, use `sk-code`.\\n\\n  Line 84: | `sk-code` | Builds what sk-design designs. sk-design decides taste and sk-code writes the code. |\\n\\n  Line 85: | `mcp-open-design` | Transport for design work. It never decides taste, so it co-loads sk-design. |\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/design-motion/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 236: 2. Decide the motion budget: one hero moment, local feedback layer, state transitions, or no motion.\\n\\n\\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-design/SKILL.md:\\n  Line 3: description: \\\"Distinctive, intentional UI design and the full design surface: visual direction, taste, and build for ... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":42,"totalLines":43,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/009-reference-asset-expansion/research/lineages/gpt55fast/logs/fanout-lineage.out","time":{"start":1782487354754,"end":1782487354764}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_058f6305d2ff8593016a3e993a9a1881918b1f313a422d275a"}},"id":"prt_f04868d3b001tx9w2qjceYzSOM","sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","messageID":"msg_f048639bf001htKOl59Gi1m1s3"}}
