{"type":"text","timestamp":1782487516795,"sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","part":{"id":"prt_f0488d1a3001ebGtl160UrQNon","messageID":"msg_f0488bafe001arzRVbGqsdFTyD","sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","type":"text","text":"The source anchors confirm the matrix should prefer a few high-leverage, reusable artifacts over many new prose pages: operator register, pre-flight cards, and mode-specific checklist/playbook assets.","time":{"start":1782487503267,"end":1782487516794},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0cc579814642de46016a3e99cf3ed481918df93a421275e267","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782487516909,"sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_cpFotDIZsVl9YfTwIofPrHSS","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"pre-flight|preflight|CHECK|mechanical|fake|content|mock|AIDA|2-line|gapless|SECTION 01|Title Case|John Doe|Elevate","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/stitch-skill.md:\n  Line 59: - **No Filler Text:** \"Scroll to explore\", \"Swipe down\", scroll arrow icons, bouncing chevrons are BANNED. The content should pull users in naturally\n\n  Line 73: - No overlapping elements — every element occupies its own clear spatial zone. No absolute-positioned content stacking\n\n  Line 108: - No generic names (\"John Doe\", \"Acme\", \"Nexus\")\n\n  Line 109: - No fake round numbers (`99.99%`, `50%`)\n\n  Line 110: - No AI copywriting clichés (\"Elevate\", \"Seamless\", \"Unleash\", \"Next-Gen\")\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/slidev.md:\n  Line 47: More content\n\n  Line 174: | `center` | Centered content |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/taste-skill.md:\n  Line 3: description: Anti-slop frontend skill for landing pages, portfolios, and redesigns. The agent reads the brief, infers the right design direction, and ships interfaces that do not look templated. Real design systems when applicable, audit-first on redesigns, strict pre-flight check.\n\n  Line 210: * **ANTI-CENTER BIAS:** Centered Hero / H1 sections are avoided when `DESIGN_VARIANCE > 4`. Force \"Split Screen\" (50/50), \"Left-aligned content / right-aligned asset\", \"Asymmetric white-space\", or scroll-pinned structures.\n\n  Line 225: * **BUTTON CONTRAST CHECK (mandatory, a11y):** Before shipping any button, verify the button text is readable against the button background. White button + white text, `bg-white` CTA with `text-white` label, transparent button against the page background with no border → all banned. Audit every CTA: contrast ratio WCAG AA min (4.5:1 for body, 3:1 for large text 18px+). Same rule applies to ghost buttons over photographic backgrounds (use a backdrop, scrim, or stroke).\n\n  Line 228: * **FORM CONTRAST CHECK (mandatory, a11y):** Form inputs, placeholder text, focus rings, helper text, and error text all pass WCAG AA contrast against the section background. Light placeholders on a near-white form, white form on white page section, form labels grayer than 4.5:1 contrast → all banned. Audit every form before shipping.\n\n  Line 238: * **HERO TOP PADDING CAP (mandatory):** Hero top padding max `pt-24` (≈6rem) at desktop. More than that means the hero content floats halfway down the viewport and reads as a layout bug, not as intentional space. If your hero needs more breathing room, increase font scale or asset size, not top padding.\n\n  Line 250: * **BENTO CELL COUNT RULE (mandatory):** A bento grid has EXACTLY as many cells as you have content for. 3 items → 3 cells (1+2 split, or 2+1, or asymmetric trio). 5 items → 5 cells (2+3, 3+2, hero+4, etc.). If your grid has an empty cell in the middle or at the end, you planned wrong. Re-shape the grid; do not paste a blank tile.\n\n  Line 256:   - **Pre-Flight Check is mechanical:** count instances of `uppercase tracking` (or similar small-caps mono labels above headlines) across all section components. If count > ceil(sectionCount / 3), the output fails.\n\n  Line 264: Landing pages and portfolios are **visual products**. Text-only pages with fake-screenshot divs are slop.\n\n  Line 272: 3. **Last resort: tell the user.** If neither is possible, do NOT fill the page with hand-rolled SVG illustrations or div-based \"fake screenshots.\" Instead, leave clearly-labeled placeholder slots (`<!-- TODO: hero product photo, 1600x1200 -->`) and at the end of the response say: *\"This page needs real images at: \\[list of placements\\]. Please generate or provide them.\"*\n\n  Line 290: **Div-based fake screenshots are banned.** A \"hand-built product preview\" rendered with `<div>` rectangles, fake task lists, fake dashboards, fake terminal windows is a Tell. If you need to show a product:\n\n  Line 302: * **Default content shape per section:** short headline (≤ 8 words) + short sub-paragraph (≤ 25 words) + one visual asset OR one CTA. Anything more must be justified by the section's job.\n\n  Line 325:   - **Reads like an LLM trying to sound thoughtful** (passive-aggressive humility, fake-craftsman labels, mock-poetic micro-meta)\n\n  Line 329:   - Are explicitly labeled as mock (`<!-- mock -->`, \"example\", \"sample data\") - fine\n\n  Line 330:   - Are AI-invented spec aesthetics - banned. Don't fake engineering precision the brand doesn't claim.\n\n  Line 360: * **MOTION MUST BE MOTIVATED (mandatory).** Before adding any animation, ask: \"what does this animation communicate?\" Valid answers: hierarchy (drawing attention to the right thing), storytelling (revealing content in sequence that matches a narrative), feedback (acknowledging a user action), state transition (showing something changed). Invalid answer: \"it looked cool\". GSAP everywhere because GSAP is available is amateur. Each ScrollTrigger, each marquee, each pinned section needs a reason. If you cannot articulate the reason in one sentence, drop the animation.\n\n  Line 361: * **MARQUEE MAX-ONE-PER-PAGE (mandatory).** Horizontal scrolling text marquees (\"logos endlessly scrolling\", \"manifesto scrolling sideways\", \"kinetic word strip\") are appropriate at most ONCE per page. Two or more marquees on the same page reads as lazy filler. Pick the one section where the marquee actually serves the content; the others get a different layout.\n\n  Line 514: * **Layout Transitions:** Use Motion's `layout` and `layoutId` props for visible state changes (re-ordering lists, expanding modals, shared elements between routes). Do not wrap static content in `layout` props \"for safety\" - it costs measurement work.\n\n  Line 616: * **NO generic names.** \"John Doe\", \"Sarah Chan\", \"Jack Su\" → use creative, realistic, locale-appropriate names.\n\n  Line 618: * **NO fake-perfect numbers.** Avoid `99.99%`, `50%`, `1234567`. Use organic, messy data (`47.2%`, `+1 (312) 847-1928`).\n\n  Line 620: * **NO filler verbs.** \"Elevate\", \"Seamless\", \"Unleash\", \"Next-Gen\", \"Revolutionize\" → concrete verbs only.\n\n  Line 625: * **NO div-based fake screenshots.** Never build a fake product UI out of `<div>` rectangles to simulate a screenshot. Use real images, generated images, or skip the preview.\n\n  Line 652: * **NO crosshair / hairline grid lines as decoration.** Vertical and horizontal lines drawn just to make the page \"feel designed\" - banned. Use them only when they organize real content.\n\n  Line 655: * **NO div-based fake product UI in the hero** (fake task list, fake terminal, fake dashboard built from styled divs). It is the #1 LLM-design Tell. Use a real screenshot, a generated image, a real component preview, or none at all.\n\n  Line 656: * **NO fake version footers** (\"v0.6.2-rc.1\", \"last sync 4s ago · main\") inside fake screenshots. Adds nothing, screams AI.\n\n  Line 661: * **NO \"We respect the French ones\"-style** mock-humble industry-references in body copy. Cute and AI-y.\n\n  Line 664: * **NO generic step labels.** \"Stage 1 / Stage 2 / Stage 3\", \"Step 1 / Step 2 / Step 3\", \"Phase 01 / Phase 02 / Phase 03\", \"Pass One / Pass Two / Pass Three\". Banned. The actual step content is the label. If you must show progression, use the verb-noun directly (\"Install\", \"Configure\", \"Ship\") not \"Stage 1: Install\".\n\n  Line 669: * **NO version footers on marketing pages.** Footer strings like `v1.4.2`, `Build 0048`, `last sync 4s ago · main` are CLI / devtool fixtures, not landing-page content. Banned on marketing/landing/portfolio pages.\n\n  Line 715: * **Scroll-Pinned Hero** - Hero stays pinned while content scrolls behind.\n\n  Line 724: * **Mega Menu Reveal** - Full-screen dropdown, stagger-fade content.\n\n  Line 790: * **Redesign - Overhaul** - new visual language on top of existing content. Treat as greenfield for visuals; preserve content and IA.\n\n  Line 807: * **Preserve copy voice** unless asked for a rewrite. Visual modernisation ≠ content rewrite.\n\n  Line 821: * IA, content, and SEO sound → **targeted evolution** (Levers 1-4). ~70% of value at ~40% of risk.\n\n  Line 822: * Visual debt is structural (broken IA, no design system, broken mobile) → **full redesign** with strict content preservation.\n\n  Line 910: ## 14. FINAL PRE-FLIGHT CHECK\n\n  Line 931: - [ ] **Hero top padding**: max `pt-24` at desktop, hero content does not float halfway down the viewport?\n\n  Line 933: - [ ] **EYEBROW COUNT (mechanical)**: count instances of `uppercase tracking` micro-labels above section headlines across all components. Count ≤ ceil(sectionCount / 3)? Hero counts as 1.\n\n  Line 947: - [ ] **Real images used** (gen-tool first, then Picsum-seed, then explicit placeholder slots) - NO div-based fake screenshots, NO hand-rolled decorative SVGs, NO pure-text minimalism?\n\n  Line 961: - [ ] **Content density** sane: no 20-row data tables, no fake-precise specs without justification, ≤ 25-word sub-paragraphs by default?\n\n  Line 985: The sections below are vendored reference content. They give the agent real install commands, real canonical doc links, and real working starter snippets for each design system named in Section 2. Use them to ground decisions in production reality, not training-data fiction.\n\n  Line 1029: #   <meta name=\"shopify-api-key\" content=\"%SHOPIFY_API_KEY%\" />\n\n  Line 1161:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 1173:   content: \"\";\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/layout.md:\n  Line 46:    - Does density match the content type? (Data-dense UIs need tighter spacing; marketing pages need more air)\n\n  Line 56: - **Layout approach**: What structure fits the content? Flex for 1D, Grid for 2D, named areas for complex page layouts.\n\n  Line 74: - **Asymmetric compositions**: a deliberate choice when the content invites it (not a default to chase).\n\n  Line 78: - **Use Flexbox for 1D layouts**: Rows of items, nav bars, button groups, card contents, most component internals.\n\n  Line 81: - Use **container queries** for components, viewport queries for page layouts. A card in a narrow sidebar can stay compact while the same card in a main content area expands automatically:\n\n  Line 94: - Use cards only when content is truly distinct and actionable. Never nest cards inside cards\n\n  Line 95: - Vary card sizes, span columns, or mix cards with non-card content to break repetition\n\n  Line 111: - Create clear content groupings through proximity and separation.\n\n  Line 127:   content: ''; position: absolute; inset: -10px;\n\n  Line 143: - **Hierarchy**: Is the most important content obvious within 2 seconds?\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/12-principles-of-animation.md:\n  Line 8:   source: /content/12-principles-of-animation/index.mdx\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/harden.md:\n  Line 75:   min-width: 0; /* Allow shrinking below content size */\n\n  Line 96: - Use flexbox/grid that adapts to content\n\n  Line 104: // ✅ Good: Adapts to content\n\n  Line 263: - Skip links for long content\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/bencium-innovative-ux-designer.md:\n  Line 38: - **Industrial/utilitarian** - functional, no-nonsense, mechanical precision\n\n  Line 99:    - Embrace functional depth: modals over content, dropdowns over UI\n\n  Line 115:    - Users should focus on content and goals, not on understanding the interface\n\n  Line 147: 2. **Hierarchy**: Is visual importance aligned with content importance?\n\n  Line 258: - **Text version**: Paragraphs and long-form content - legibility matters\n\n  Line 361: - Create clear paths through the content\n\n  Line 375:    - Users interact directly with content, not through abstract controls\n\n  Line 505: - Use skeletons until content renders\n\n  Line 526: - Use breakpoints based on content needs, not specific devices\n\n  Line 546: - Provide alternative text for images and non-text content\n\n  Line 588: - Test with different content lengths (short, long, edge cases)\n\n  Line 631: For this content hierarchy, I'm thinking:\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/output-skill.md:\n  Line 18: **In prose:** \"Let me know if you want me to continue\", \"I can provide more details if needed\", \"for brevity\", \"the rest follows the same pattern\", \"similarly for the remaining\", \"and so on\" (when replacing actual content), \"I'll leave that as an exercise\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/pseudo-elements.md:\n  Line 8:   source: /content/taking-advantage-of-pseudo-elements/index.mdx\n\n  Line 33: #### `pseudo-content-required`\n\n  Line 34: ::before and ::after require content property to render.\n\n  Line 47:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 54: Use pseudo-elements for decorative content instead of extra DOM nodes.\n\n  Line 72:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 83:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 97:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 104: Pseudo-elements need z-index to layer correctly with content.\n\n  Line 109:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 125:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 150:   content: \"\";\n\n  Line 316: components/button/styles.module.css:12 - [pseudo-content-required] ::before missing content property\n\n  Line 326: | `pseudo-content-required` | 2 | HIGH |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/gpt-tasteskill.md:\n  Line 3: description: Elite UX/UI & Advanced GSAP Motion Engineer. Enforces Python-driven true randomization for layout variance, strict AIDA page structure, wide editorial typography (bans 6-line wraps), gapless bento grids, strict GSAP ScrollTriggers (pinning, stacking, scrubbing), inline micro-images, and massive section spacing.\n\n  Line 7: You are an elite, award-winning frontend design engineer. Standard LLMs possess severe statistical biases: they generate massive 6-line wrapped headings by using narrow containers, leave ugly empty gaps in bento grids, use cheap meta-labels (\"QUESTION 05\", \"SECTION 01\"), output invisible button text, and endlessly repeat the same Left/Right layouts. \n\n  Line 22: ## 2. AIDA STRUCTURE & SPACING\n\n  Line 24: The rest of the page MUST follow the AIDA framework:\n\n  Line 57: - **Horizontal Accordions:** Vertical slices that expand horizontally on hover to reveal content and imagery.\n\n  Line 62: - **The Meta-Label Ban:** BANNED FOREVER are labels like \"SECTION 01\", \"SECTION 04\", \"QUESTION 05\", \"ABOUT US\". Remove them entirely. They look cheap and unprofessional.\n\n  Line 69: 1. **Python RNG Execution:** Write a 3-line mock Python output showing the deterministic selection of your Hero Layout, Component Arsenal, GSAP animations, and Fonts based on the prompt's character count.\n\n  Line 70: 2. **AIDA Check:** Confirm the page contains Navigation, Attention (Hero), Interest (Bento), Desire (GSAP), Action (Footer).\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/polish.md:\n  Line 81: - **Empty, loading, and arrival transitions**: How content arrives, updates, and leaves matches how it does in adjacent features.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"pre-flight|preflight|CHECK|mechanical|fake|content|mock|AIDA|2-line|gapless|SECTION 01|Title Case|John Doe|Elevate","time":{"start":1782487516876,"end":1782487516907}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0cc579814642de46016a3e99dc9fd48191bc7db54f25f8d53b"}},"id":"prt_f04890681001bshIYtXgJI44ii","sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","messageID":"msg_f0488bafe001arzRVbGqsdFTyD"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782487516922,"sessionID":"ses_0fb835c90ffeqUAmvkS8gfEWSy","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_aBEMZC6CMnM3NXg06KqfDYC3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"data-viz|data visualization|chart|dashboard|graph|visualization","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main","include":"*.md"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/README.md:\n  Line 72: | ui-design | 14 | 4 | Craft polished interfaces: layout grids, color systems, typography, responsive design, data viz, and Gestalt/perceptual principles. |\n\n  Line 77: | visual-critique | 7 | 2 | Visual critique: hierarchy, brand consistency, composition, typography, colour, affordance, and information density. |\n\n  Line 95: | `/ui-design:type-system` | ui-design | Create a complete typography system. |\n\n  Line 150: Drop a screenshot. Get a prioritised fix list covering hierarchy, brand consistency, composition, and typography. This tells you what's actually broken before you add anything new.\n\n  Line 171: | Typography system | ui-design | `/ui-design:type-system` |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/154-sk-design-parent/external/designer-skills-main/design-research/skills/user-persona/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Create refined user personas from research data with demographics, goals, frustrations, and behavioral patterns. Use when synthesizing user research into actionable persona profiles for design decisions.\n\n  Line 16: - Personas (Alan Cooper, About Face): Archetypical users based on behavioral patterns, not demographics alone.\n\n  Line 29:    - Demographics: age range,